# Query to get new users by date
new_users_query = f"""
SELECT 
    event_date,
    version,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_name = 'first_open' THEN user_pseudo_id END) as new_users
FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock`
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
	AND version IN ({', '.join([f"'{x}'" for x in new_user_per_version.head(4)['version']])})
GROUP BY event_date, version
ORDER BY event_date;
"""
new_users = client.query(new_users_query).to_dataframe()

# Convert event_date to datetime for proper sorting
new_users['event_date'] = pd.to_datetime(new_users['event_date'], format='%Y%m%d')

# Set the style
sns.set_style("whitegrid")

# Get 6 distinctive colors from a more vibrant colormap
colors = sns.color_palette("husl", n_colors=6)

# Create the visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Create a dictionary mapping versions to colors
versions = new_users['version'].unique()
color_dict = dict(zip(versions, colors))

# Plot each version with a specific color
for version, color in color_dict.items():
    version_data = new_users[new_users['version'] == version].sort_values('event_date')
    plt.plot(version_data['event_date'], version_data['new_users'], label=version, color=color)

# Add vertical lines for key dates
key_dates = ['20250204', '20250211', '20250213', '20250220', '20250221', '20250228']
for date in key_dates:
    plt.axvline(x=pd.to_datetime(date, format='%Y%m%d'), 
                color='gray', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)

# Customize the plot
plt.title('Daily New Users Trend by Version', pad=20)
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Number of New Users')
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(title='Version')
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()

users_by_country_query = f"""
SELECT 
    version,
    country,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_name = 'first_open' THEN user_pseudo_id END) as new_users
FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock`
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
    AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
        OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
        OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
GROUP BY country, version;
"""

users_by_country = client.query(users_by_country_query).to_dataframe()

# Get top 10 countries by total users
top_10_countries = users_by_country.groupby('country')['new_users'].sum().nlargest(10).index

# Filter for top 10 countries
users_by_country_filtered = users_by_country[users_by_country['country'].isin(top_10_countries)]

# Calculate total users per country for sorting
country_totals = users_by_country_filtered.groupby('country')['new_users'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
users_by_country_filtered['country'] = pd.Categorical(
    users_by_country_filtered['country'], 
    categories=country_totals.index, 
    ordered=True
)

# Set the style
sns.set_style("whitegrid")

# Create the visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Create grouped bar plot
ax = sns.barplot(data=users_by_country_filtered, 
                 x='country', 
                 y='new_users',
                 hue='version',
                 palette=color_dict
                 )

# Customize the plot
plt.title('New Users by Country and Version (Top 10 Countries)', pad=20)
plt.xlabel('Country')
plt.ylabel('Number of New Users')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(title='Version')
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()

RETENTION¶

In [12]:
query = f"""
WITH cohort AS (
    SELECT 
        user_pseudo_id,
        PARSE_DATE('%Y%m%d', event_date) as cohort_date,
        version
    FROM (
        SELECT * 
        FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` 
        WHERE platform = 'IOS'
            AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
                OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
                OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
        )
    WHERE event_name = 'first_open'
),
cohort_sizes AS (
    SELECT
        cohort_date,
        version,
        COUNT(DISTINCT user_pseudo_id) as total_users
    FROM cohort 
    GROUP BY cohort_date, version
),
daily_retention AS (
    SELECT 
        c.cohort_date,
        c.version,
        DATE_DIFF(PARSE_DATE('%Y%m%d', e.event_date), c.cohort_date, DAY) as days_since_first_open,
        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN (event_name = 'session_start' OR event_name = 'first_open') THEN e.user_pseudo_id END) as retained_users,
        cs.total_users
    FROM cohort c
    LEFT JOIN (
        SELECT * 
        FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` 
        WHERE platform = 'IOS'
            AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
                OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
                OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
        ) e
        ON c.user_pseudo_id = e.user_pseudo_id
            AND PARSE_DATE('%Y%m%d', e.event_date) >= c.cohort_date
            AND c.version = e.version
    JOIN cohort_sizes cs
        ON c.cohort_date = cs.cohort_date
            AND c.version = cs.version
    GROUP BY c.cohort_date, c.version, days_since_first_open, cs.total_users
)
SELECT 
    cohort_date,
    version,
    days_since_first_open,
    retained_users,
    total_users,
    ROUND(retained_users * 100.0 / total_users, 2) as retention_rate
FROM daily_retention
WHERE days_since_first_open <= 14
ORDER BY version, cohort_date, days_since_first_open;
"""

# Execute the query and load results into a pandas DataFrame
retention = client.query(query).to_dataframe()
In [13]:
# Create a figure with 3 subplots in one row
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(27, 7))

for idx, version in enumerate(retention['version'].unique()):
    retention_temp = retention[(retention['version'] == version) & (retention['days_since_first_open'] <= 8)]
    # Pivot the data for the heatmap
    retention_pivot = retention_temp.pivot(
        index='cohort_date',
        columns='days_since_first_open',
        values='retention_rate'
    )

    plt.sca(axes[idx])
    plt.title(f"MoM Retention Rate for Version {version}")

    sns.heatmap(data=retention_pivot, annot=True, vmin=0, vmax=40, cmap='crest', fmt=".1f")

    plt.xlabel('Days since first Open')
    plt.ylabel('Cohort Date')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

  • The above plot show the average D1, D2, etc. retention of users across all cohorts.
  • Regarding retention, version 1.29.5 have the best retention rate, followed by version 1.35.2, then the last is 1.30.
  • Version 1.30 is quite far behind compared to the other 2 versions.

query = f"""
SELECT
    country,
    SUM(CASE 
        WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN event_value_in_usd 
        ELSE 0 
    END) as iap_revenue,
    SUM(CASE 
        WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN (SELECT value.double_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'value')
        ELSE 0 
    END) as ads_revenue,
    SUM(CASE 
        WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN event_value_in_usd
        WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN (SELECT value.double_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'value')
        ELSE 0 
    END) as total_revenue
FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
    AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
        OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
        OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
	AND EXISTS (
		SELECT 1
		FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
		WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
                OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
                OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
  			AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
			AND B.event_name = "first_open"
	)
GROUP BY country
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC
"""

revenue_by_country = client.query(query).to_dataframe()

# Create a donut chart
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
plt.pie(revenue_by_country['total_revenue'], 
        labels=revenue_by_country['country'],
        autopct='%1.1f%%',
        pctdistance=0.85,
        wedgeprops=dict(width=0.5))
plt.title('Total Revenue Distribution by Country')
plt.show()

query = f"""
SELECT
	version,
	COUNT(DISTINCT user_pseudo_id) as total_users,
	SUM(CASE 
		WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN event_value_in_usd 
		ELSE 0 
	END) as iap_revenue,
	SUM(CASE 
		WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN (SELECT value.double_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'value')
		ELSE 0 
	END) as ads_revenue,
	COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN user_pseudo_id END) as paying_iap_users,
	COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN user_pseudo_id END) as show_ads_users,
	COUNT(CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' AND 
		(SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'ad_format') = 'REWARDED'
		THEN 1 END) as num_rewarded_ads,
	COUNT(CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' AND 
		(SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'ad_format') = 'INTER'
		THEN 1 END) as num_inter_ads,
	COUNT(CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN 1 END) as num_ads_shown
FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
    AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
        OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
        OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
	AND country = 'United States'
	AND EXISTS (
		SELECT 1
		FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
		WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
                OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
                OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
  			AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
			AND B.event_name = "first_open"
	)
GROUP BY version
"""

monetization_metrics_overall = client.query(query).to_dataframe()

# Calculate metrics
monetization_metrics_overall['pay_rate'] = monetization_metrics_overall['paying_iap_users'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['arpu'] = (monetization_metrics_overall['iap_revenue'] + monetization_metrics_overall['ads_revenue']) / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['airpu'] = monetization_metrics_overall['iap_revenue'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['aarpu'] = monetization_metrics_overall['ads_revenue'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['ads_per_user'] = monetization_metrics_overall['num_ads_shown'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['ads_shown_rate'] = monetization_metrics_overall['show_ads_users'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['arppu'] = monetization_metrics_overall['iap_revenue'] / monetization_metrics_overall['paying_iap_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['rewarded_ads_per_user'] = monetization_metrics_overall['num_rewarded_ads'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']
monetization_metrics_overall['inter_ads_per_user'] = monetization_metrics_overall['num_inter_ads'] / monetization_metrics_overall['total_users']

# Create subplots for non-ad metrics
non_ad_metrics = ['pay_rate', 'arpu', 'airpu', 'aarpu', 'arppu', 'ads_shown_rate']
fig1, axes1 = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15, 10))
axes1 = axes1.ravel()

# Plot non-ad metrics
for idx, metric in enumerate(non_ad_metrics):
    sns.barplot(data=monetization_metrics_overall, x='version', y=metric, ax=axes1[idx], hue='version', palette=color_dict, legend=False)
    axes1[idx].set_title(f'{metric.upper()} by Version')
    axes1[idx].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    axes1[idx].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Create subplot for ad-related metrics
ad_metrics = ['ads_per_user', 'rewarded_ads_per_user', 'inter_ads_per_user']
fig2, axes2 = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))
axes2 = axes2.ravel()

# Plot ad-related metrics
for idx, metric in enumerate(ad_metrics):
    sns.barplot(data=monetization_metrics_overall, x='version', y=metric, ax=axes2[idx], hue='version', palette=color_dict, legend=False)
    axes2[idx].set_title(f'{metric.upper()} by Version')
    axes2[idx].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    axes2[idx].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

query = f"""
WITH monetization_metrics AS (
	SELECT
		event_date AS date,
		version,
		COUNT(DISTINCT user_pseudo_id) as dau,
		SUM(CASE 
			WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN event_value_in_usd 
			ELSE 0 
		END) as iap_revenue,
		SUM(CASE 
			WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN (SELECT value.double_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'value')
			ELSE 0 
		END) as ads_revenue,
		COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN user_pseudo_id END) as paying_iap_users,
		COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN user_pseudo_id END) as show_ads_users,
		COUNT(CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' THEN 1 END) as num_ads_shown
	FROM (
     	SELECT * 
      	FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
       	WHERE platform = 'IOS'
			AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
				OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
				OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
            AND country = 'United States'
			AND EXISTS (
				SELECT 1
				FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
				WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
						OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
						OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
					AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
					AND B.event_name = "first_open"
			)
		)
	GROUP BY version, date
	ORDER BY version, date
)
SELECT 
	*
FROM monetization_metrics
"""

monetization_metrics_overtime = client.query(query).to_dataframe()

# Add row number for each version
monetization_metrics_overtime['day_number'] = monetization_metrics_overtime.groupby('version').cumcount() + 1

# Calculate revenue per DAU
monetization_metrics_overtime['iap_revenue_per_dau'] = monetization_metrics_overtime['iap_revenue'] / monetization_metrics_overtime['dau']
monetization_metrics_overtime['ads_revenue_per_dau'] = monetization_metrics_overtime['ads_revenue'] / monetization_metrics_overtime['dau']

# Create figure with two subplots
fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(15, 20), height_ratios=[2, 1.25, 1.25])

# Plot DAU
sns.lineplot(data=monetization_metrics_overtime, x='day_number', y='dau', hue='version', palette=color_dict, ax=ax1)
ax1.set_title('Daily Active Users (DAU) Trend', fontsize=14, pad=20)
ax1.set_xlabel('Days Since Version Launch')
ax1.set_ylabel('Number of Users')
ax1.set_ylim(bottom=0)
ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Plot IAP Revenue per DAU
sns.lineplot(data=monetization_metrics_overtime, x='day_number', y='iap_revenue_per_dau', hue='version', palette=color_dict, ax=ax2)
ax2.set_title('Daily IAP Revenue per DAU Trend', fontsize=14, pad=20)
ax2.set_xlabel('Days Since Version Launch')
ax2.set_ylabel('Revenue per User (USD)')
ax2.set_ylim(bottom=0)
ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Plot Ads Revenue per DAU
sns.lineplot(data=monetization_metrics_overtime, x='day_number', y='ads_revenue_per_dau', hue='version', palette=color_dict, ax=ax3)
ax3.set_title('Daily Ads Revenue per DAU Trend', fontsize=14, pad=20)
ax3.set_xlabel('Days Since Version Launch')
ax3.set_ylabel('Revenue per User (USD)')
ax3.set_ylim(bottom=0)
ax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
for ax in [ax1, ax2, ax3]:
    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=0, ha='center')

# Adjust layout
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

query = f"""
WITH revenue_events AS (
    -- Get all revenue events (IAP and rewarded ads)
    SELECT 
        user_pseudo_id,
        event_timestamp,
        version,
        CASE 
            WHEN event_name = 'in_app_purchase' THEN 
                event_value_in_usd
        END AS iap_revenue,
        CASE WHEN event_name = 'ad_impression' AND 
			(SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'ad_format') = 'REWARDED' THEN
			(SELECT value.double_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'value')
        END as ads_rewarded_revenue
    FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
    WHERE event_name IN ('in_app_purchase', 'ad_impression')
    	AND (event_value_in_usd IS NOT NULL OR (SELECT value.double_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'value') IS NOT NULL)
        AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
            OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
            OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
		AND country = 'United States'
		AND EXISTS (
			SELECT 1
			FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
			WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
					OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
					OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
				AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
				AND B.event_name = "first_open"
		)
),
level_events AS (
    -- Get all level start events with level number
    SELECT
        user_pseudo_id,
        event_timestamp,
        version,
        (SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'level') as level
    FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
    WHERE event_name = 'start_level'
    	AND (SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'level') IS NOT NULL
        AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
            OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
            OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
		AND country = 'United States'
		AND EXISTS (
			SELECT 1
			FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
			WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
					OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
					OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
				AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
				AND B.event_name = "first_open"
		)
),
revenue_with_levels AS (
    -- Join revenue events with their closest preceding level start
    SELECT 
        r.user_pseudo_id,
        r.version,
        COALESCE(r.iap_revenue, 0) as iap_revenue,
        COALESCE(r.ads_rewarded_revenue, 0) as ads_revenue,
        l.level,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY r.user_pseudo_id, r.event_timestamp 
            ORDER BY ABS(l.event_timestamp - r.event_timestamp)
        ) as rn
    FROM revenue_events r
    LEFT JOIN level_events l
        ON r.user_pseudo_id = l.user_pseudo_id
        	AND l.event_timestamp <= r.event_timestamp
)
SELECT
    le.version,
    le.level,
    COUNT(DISTINCT le.user_pseudo_id) as num_users,
    SUM(COALESCE(rwl.iap_revenue, 0)) as iap_revenue,
    SUM(COALESCE(rwl.ads_revenue, 0)) as ads_revenue,
    SUM(COALESCE(rwl.iap_revenue, 0)) / COUNT(DISTINCT le.user_pseudo_id) as iap_revenue_per_user,
    SUM(COALESCE(rwl.ads_revenue, 0)) / COUNT(DISTINCT le.user_pseudo_id) as ads_revenue_per_user
FROM level_events le
LEFT JOIN revenue_with_levels rwl
    ON le.user_pseudo_id = rwl.user_pseudo_id
		AND le.level = rwl.level
		AND rwl.rn = 1
GROUP BY version, level
ORDER BY version, CAST(level AS INT64)

"""

monetization_metrics_by_level = client.query(query).to_dataframe()
In [27]:
# Filter data to levels <= 100
monetization_metrics_by_level = monetization_metrics_by_level[monetization_metrics_by_level['level'].astype(int) <= 100]

# Convert level columns to same type before merging
monetization_metrics_by_level['level'] = monetization_metrics_by_level['level'].astype(str)
level_metrics['level'] = level_metrics['level'].astype(str)

# Merge with level_metrics
merged_df = monetization_metrics_by_level.merge(level_metrics[['version', 'level', 'win_rate']], 
                                              on=['version', 'level'], how='left')

# Calculate metrics
merged_df['total_revenue'] = merged_df['iap_revenue'] + merged_df['ads_revenue']
merged_df['total_revenue_per_user'] = merged_df['total_revenue'] / merged_df['num_users']
merged_df['revenue_times_win_rate'] = merged_df['total_revenue'] * merged_df['win_rate']
merged_df['revenue_per_user_times_win_rate'] = merged_df['total_revenue_per_user'] * merged_df['win_rate']
merged_df['ads_revenue_per_user_times_win_rate'] = merged_df['ads_revenue_per_user'] * merged_df['win_rate']

merged_df = merged_df[merged_df['version'] != '0.7.21']

# Create figures
fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 6))

# Plot ads revenue per user times win rate by level
sns.lineplot(data=merged_df, x='level', y='ads_revenue_per_user_times_win_rate', hue='version', palette=color_dict, ax=ax1)
ax1.set_title('Ads Revenue per User times Win Rate by Level', fontsize=14, pad=20)
ax1.set_xlabel('Level')
ax1.set_ylabel('Ads Revenue per User times Win Rate (USD)')
ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
ax1.xaxis.set_major_locator(plt.MaxNLocator(10))

plt.show()

# Create figures for rolling averages
fig2, ax2 = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 6))

# Plot rolling averages
for version in merged_df['version'].unique():
    version_data = merged_df[merged_df['version'] == version].sort_values('level')
    
    # Ads revenue per user times win rate rolling average
    rolling_avg = version_data['ads_revenue_per_user_times_win_rate'].rolling(window=10).mean()
    ax2.plot(version_data['level'], rolling_avg, label=version, linewidth=2, color=color_dict[version])

ax2.set_title('Rolling Average (10) of Ads Revenue per User times Win Rate by Level', fontsize=14, pad=20)

query = f"""
SELECT 
	version,
	CAST((
		SELECT value.string_value 
		FROM UNNEST(event_params) 
		WHERE key = "level"
		) AS INT64) as level,
	COUNT(DISTINCT user_pseudo_id) as num_users
FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
    AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
        OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
        OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
	AND event_name = "start_level"
	AND EXISTS (
		SELECT 1
		FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
		WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
				OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220') 
				OR (version = '0.7.13' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250221' AND '20250228'))
			AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
			AND B.event_name = "first_open"
	)
GROUP BY version, level
"""

level_churn = client.query(query).to_dataframe()

# Get number of users at level 1 for each version
level_1_users = level_churn[level_churn['level'] == 1].set_index('version')['num_users']

# Calculate retention rate relative to level 1
level_churn['retention_rate'] = level_churn.apply(
    lambda row: row['num_users'] / level_1_users[row['version']], 
    axis=1
)

# Create visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Plot each version
for version in level_churn['version'].unique():
    version_data = level_churn[level_churn['version'] == version]
    version_data.sort_values('level', inplace=True)
    plt.plot(version_data['level'], version_data['retention_rate'], 
             label=version, color=color_dict[version])

plt.title('Level Retention Rate by Version')
plt.xlabel('Level Number') 
plt.ylabel('Retention Rate (relative to Level 1)')
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
plt.legend(title='Version')
plt.ylim(0, 1)
plt.show()

query = f"""
WITH level_progress_per_user AS (
	SELECT
		event_date,
		version,
		user_pseudo_id,
		MIN(CASE WHEN event_name = 'start_level' THEN (SELECT CAST(value.string_value AS INT64) FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'level') END) as min_level,
		MAX(CASE WHEN event_name = 'win_level' THEN (SELECT CAST(value.string_value AS INT64) FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = 'level') END) as max_level
	FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` A
	WHERE platform = 'IOS'
		AND ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
			OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220')

			SELECT 1
			FROM `royal-hexa-in-house.pixon_data_science.003_mock` B
			WHERE ((version = '0.7.9' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250204' AND '20250211')
					OR (version = '0.7.12' AND event_date BETWEEN '20250213' AND '20250220')

				AND A.user_pseudo_id = B.user_pseudo_id
				AND B.event_name = "first_open"
		)
	GROUP BY version, event_date, user_pseudo_id
)
SELECT 
	event_date, 
 	version, 
  	COUNT(DISTINCT user_pseudo_id) as num_users,
	AVG(max_level - min_level) as avg_level_progress

		CAST((SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = "level") AS INT64) as level,
		CAST((SELECT value.string_value FROM UNNEST(event_params) WHERE key = "timeplay") AS INT64) as timeplay
	FROM cleaned_data
	WHERE event_name = 'win_level'
)
SELECT
	version,
	level,
	AVG(timeplay) as avg_completion_time_seconds
FROM level_win
GROUP BY version, level
"""

level_completion_times = client.query(query).to_dataframe()

# Create visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(18, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=level_completion_times.query('level <= 100'), 
             x='level', 
			 y='avg_completion_time_seconds', 
			 hue='version', 
			 palette=color_dict)

plt.title('Average Level Completion Time by Version')
plt.xlabel('Level')
plt.ylabel('Average Completion Time (seconds)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Only show some x-axis ticks to avoid overcrowding
plt.xticks(range(0, 101, 10))
plt.show()
